sri-project-1 | Biocrude Oil from Algal Biomass | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/hydrothermal-liquefaction-pathways-low-nitrogen-biocrude-wet-algae | description:An SRI-led team is improving a new two-step process for the production of transportation fuels from microalgae.
sri-project-2 | Carbon Capture from IGCC Gas Streams Using AC-ABC Process | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/carbon-capture-igcc | description:SRI's process produces pure hydrogen while capturing carbon dioxide and acid gases.
sri-project-3 | Coal to Liquid Fuels via Methanol | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/coal-liquid-methanol | description:SRI has developed a green, cost-effective approach to create liquid fuels from existing natural resources.
sri-project-4 | Conformable Natural Gas Tanks | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/low-cost-conformable-natural-gas-tanks | description:SRI is developing a safe, low-pressure, conformable natural gas tank for light-duty vehicles.
sri-project-5 | Cyber Security Research & Development Center | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/csrdc | description:SRI provides technical, management, and subject matter expert support for the wide range of research, development, testing, evaluation, and transition activities conducted through the Center.
sri-project-6 | FRASTA: Fracture Surface Topography Analysis | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/frasta | description:SRI has developed a breakthrough technology for diagnosing and predicting fatigue failure in pipelines, aircraft, bridges, power plants, and other structures using quantitative 3D fractography.
sri-project-7 | High-Temp Membrane for Energy-Efficient Gas Separation | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/high-temperature-membrane-energy-efficient-gas-separation | description:SRI’s hollow fiber membrane separates hydrogen from carbon dioxide at high temperatures and improves the economics of carbon capture from IGCC plants.
sri-project-8 | Low-Cost Production of Titanium Alloys | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/low-cost-production-titanium-alloys | description:SRI is developing an advanced process that reacts titanium tetrachloride and other metal chlorides with hydrogen to produce titanium or titanium alloy granules in a single step.
sri-project-9 | MIMS Integrated with a Multiple-Filter Deep Water Filtration System | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/mims-integrated-multiple-filter-deep-water-filtration-system | description:For the Department of Energy, SRI and partners studied methane hydrate deposits in the Gulf of Mexico.
sri-project-10 | Mixed Salt Process for Carbon Dioxide Separation | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/mixed-salt-process-carbon-dioxide-separation | description:SRI’s mixed salt process uses known solvents in a new way to dramatically improve the economics of carbon capture.
